### ============================================

### Weekend Prediction - Short horizon over weekend
### Tests ONNX model's weekend feature handling
### Note: 2024-12-20 is Friday, 2024-12-22 is Sunday (includes weekend)
POST {{baseUrl}}/predict
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "product_id": "PROD_WEEKEND",
  "store_id": "STORE_WEEKEND",
  "start_date": "2024-12-20",
  "end_date": "2024-12-22"
}

### ============================================
### Error Cases (for testing validation)
### ============================================

### Invalid Request - Missing required field
POST {{baseUrl}}/predict
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "product_id": "PROD001",
  "start_date": "2024-12-17",
  "end_date": "2024-12-23"
}

### ============================================

### Invalid Request - End date before start date
POST {{baseUrl}}/predict
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "product_id": "PROD001",
  "store_id": "STORE001",
  "start_date": "2024-12-23",
  "end_date": "2024-12-17"
}

### ============================================

### Invalid Request - Empty product_id
POST {{baseUrl}}/predict
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "product_id": "",
  "store_id": "STORE001",
  "start_date": "2024-12-17",
  "end_date": "2024-12-23"
}

### ============================================
### Notes:
### 
### 1. To use ONNX backend, set environment variable before starting server:
###    Windows PowerShell: $env:MODEL_BACKEND="onnx"
###    Windows CMD: set MODEL_BACKEND=onnx
###    Linux/Mac: export MODEL_BACKEND=onnx
###
### 2. To use custom ONNX model:
###    $env:MODEL_BACKEND="onnx"
###    $env:MODEL_PATH="path/to/your/model.onnx"
###
### 3. The ONNX model expects features:
###    - horizon_step (1 to N, calculated from date range)
###    - day_of_week (0=Monday, 6=Sunday)
###    - month (1-12)
###    - is_weekend (1.0 if Sat/Sun, 0.0 otherwise)
###
### 4. The horizon is automatically calculated from start_date to end_date (inclusive)
###    Example: start_date="2024-12-17", end_date="2024-12-23" = 7 days
###
### 5. The model outputs predicted quantities for each day in the date range
### ============================================

